nodes.text: Jaime King (born April 23, 1979) is an American actress who provided the voice of bounty hunter Aurra Sing, thief Cassie Cryar, and the Force Priestesses in Star Wars: The Clone Wars. She is known for her roles in Bulletproof Monk, Sin City, The Spirit, Fanboys, and Hart of Dixie. She also played the role of "Axis Mary" in George Lucas' Red Tails.
